# analyze-etl CLI

Zero-persistence sales analytics pipeline. Drop a CSV or Excel file in, get instant KPIs and breakdowns in your terminal — no server, no database, no setup beyond Docker.

---

## Project Structure

```
analyze-etl/
├── pipeline.py          ← ETL core — the only file you ever edit
├── analyze-etl.py       ← CLI entry point (typer + rich)
├── requirements.txt     ← 4 packages
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
└── data/                ← drop your CSV / XLSX files here
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/mohamedtarek77/analyze-etl.git
cd analyze-etl

# 2. Build the Docker image (one time)
docker compose build

# 3. Run analysis on any file in data/
docker compose run --rm analyze-etl data/sales.csv
```

That's it. Results print directly in your terminal.

---

## Usage

### Analyze a file
```bash
docker compose run --rm analyze-etl data/sales.csv
```

Prints a formatted terminal report with:
- Key Performance Indicators (revenue, profit, orders, avg order value, margin)
- Monthly Sales — last 6 months
- Top 5 Products by revenue
- Sales by Region
- Sales by Category

### Raw JSON output
```bash
docker compose run --rm analyze-etl data/sales.csv --json
```

Useful for piping into other tools or scripts.

### Use your own file
Drop any CSV or Excel file into the `data/` folder, then pass its path:
```bash
docker compose run --rm analyze-etl data/my_q1_report.xlsx
```

---

## Required Columns

Your file must have these columns (aliases are accepted):

| Column | Accepted aliases |
|---|---|
| `order_id` | `orderid`, `order id` |
| `product_name` | `productname`, `product name`, `product` |
| `category` | — |
| `quantity` | `qty`, `units` |
| `price` | `unit_price`, `unit price`, `selling_price` |
| `cost` | `unit_cost`, `unit cost` |
| `order_date` | `date`, `sale_date` |
| `region` | `area`, `zone` |

