## How It Works

```
your file (CSV / XLSX)
        │
        ▼
  pipeline.py
  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
  │  1. load     read CSV or Excel  │
  │  2. clean    types, nulls, cols │
  │  3. derive   revenue, profit    │
  │  4. aggregate KPIs + breakdowns │
  └─────────────────────────────────┘
        │
        ▼
  analytics dict
        │
        ▼
  analyze-etl.py  →  rich terminal tables
```

The pipeline is stateless — nothing is stored between runs. Every `docker compose run` starts fresh.

